	Tired Clint    
	London, May 29 (PTI): Actor and director Clint Eastwood is tired of seeing himself on screen and wants younger actors to take over now. Eastwood, who will turn 80 on Monday, prefers to stay behind the camera but insisted that he has no plans to quit acting altogether. I leave that to younger actors now. Im not a prize fighter who has to capture another victory.    
	Older Juliet    
	 London (PTI): Actress Juliette Binoche thinks growing older has liberated her because she feels more free in the choices she makes. The Chocolat star thinks she is more honest in the choices in her life as she is no longer restricted by her past.     
	Sarah fear    
	London (PTI): Actress Sarah Jessica Parker may have amassed a fortune playing Carrie Bradshaw in Sex And The City but she is still haunted by her impoverished childhood and her biggest fear is that one day she will lose it all. Parker, 45, and her siblings had to survive on welfare money during her childhood after her father Stephen walked out on her mother Barbara when she was small.                                                                                                                                                       
